The '''Cascata dos Anjos''' (''Angels Waterfall'') is a [[waterfall]] located in the [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] of Anjos, [[concelho|municipality]] of [[Ponta do Sol]], on the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] island of [[Madeira Island|Madeira]].
The waterfall cascades over the rockface onto the old E.R.101 regional roadway, and spills into the sea below.<ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.europeanwaterfalls.com/waterfalls/anjos-cascata-dos/ | title = Anjos, cascata dos | accessdate = 22 September 2018}} </ref><ref> {{cite web | url = https://mind-the-map.com/favourite-non-touristy-places-madeira-island/ | title = My favourite non-touristy places on Madeira island | accessdate = 22 September 2018}} </ref>
